  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA219-kiḷavi">itu varaiviṭai vaittup piriya vāṟṟāḷāya talaimakaḷ tōḻikkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what SHE who was unable to bear it when [HE] separated after having fixed the time of marriage said to the confidante.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA219">
<l>            kaṇṇun tōḷun taṇṇaṟuṅ katuppum</l>
<l>            paḻanala miḻantu pacalai pāya</l>
<l>            viṉṉuyir perumpiṟi tāyiṉu meṉṉatūum</l>
<l>            pulavēṉ vāḻi tōḻi ciṟukā</l>
<l>            lalavaṉoṭu peyarum pulavuttirai naḷikaṭaṟ </l>
<l>            perumīṉ koḷḷuñ ciṟukuṭip paratavar</l>
<l>            kaṅkuṉ māṭṭiya kaṉaikati roṇcuṭar</l>
<l>            mutirā ñāyiṟ ṟetiroḷi kaṭukkuṅ</l>
<l>            kāṉalam peruntuṟaic cērppaṉ</l>
<l>            ṟāṉē yāṉē puṇarnta māṟē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">Even if [my] sweet life becomes greatly different,<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">perum piṟitu āku/uṟu</term>: this idiom is traditionally interpreted as a metaphor for death (cf. KT 17, 69, 302).</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">when eyes and shoulder and cool fragrant hair</l>
<l rend="indent2">have lost [their] old goodness while pallor has spread,</l>
<l>I won’t be vexed at all, oh friend,</l>
<l rend="indent4">because he and I<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">tāṉē yāṉē</term>: what is the exact rhetoric valence of this strangely placed double mark? Is it an emphasis of singling out, HE as well as I (both of their own free will, as T.V.G. points out)?</note> have united,</l>
<l>the man from the coast of big ghats with seashore groves,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the bright light with intense beams kindled at night</l>
<l rend="indent2">by the fishermen in small hamlets, who take big fish from the</l>
<l rend="indent2">the vast sea with fish-reeking waves that returns</l>
<l rend="indent2">with small-legged crabs,</l>
<l rend="indent">resembles the reflected brightness of the rising sun.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
